{% comment %}
Meal Plan — one quarter of a 2x2 mashup. Same list treatment as
half_vertical.liquid: a .label--outline weekday chip and the meals as
.title--large text, flowing on one line (see half_vertical.liquid for why
this doesn't use .item's .meta/.index, for the fixed chip min-width, and for
why .content, the inner .flex row, AND the title all need the .stretch
utility — .item .content sets align-items:flex-start, which shrink-wraps its
own children, so stretching .content alone isn't enough; skip any one of the
three and the width TRMNL's data-clamp script measures is undetermined
again).
Tighter limit since the tile is a quarter of the space.
{% endcomment %}
<div class="layout">
  <div class="grid grid--cols-1 gap--xsmall">
    {% for day in days limit:3 %}
      <div class="item">
        <div class="content stretch">
          <div class="flex flex--center-y gap--small stretch">
            <span class="label label--large label--outline" style="display: inline-block; min-width: 3.2em; text-align: center;">{{ day.dayName }}</span>
            <span class="title title--large stretch" data-clamp="1">
              {% if day.meals.size > 0 %}{{ day.meals | join: ", " }}{% else %}Inga måltider planerade{% endif %}
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</div>

<div class="title_bar">
  <span class="title">Matsedel</span>
</div>
